      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:22:2",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ فِي الرَّجُلِ يَقْتُلُ مَمْلُوكَهُ مُتَعَمِّداً قَالَ يُعْجِبُنِي أَنْ يُعْتِقَ رَقَبَةً وَ يَصُومَ شَهْرَيْنِ مُتَتَابِعَيْنِ وَ يُطْعِمَ سِتِّينَ مِسْكِيناً ثُمَّ تَكُونَ التَّوْبَةُ بَعْدَ ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said regarding the man who kills his slave deliberately. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘I<sup>asws</sup> would like it if he would emancipate a neck, and Fasts for two months consecutively, and feed sixty poor (persons), then there would happen to be repentance (for him) after that’."
        ]
      }
    },
